title: NEIC, USGS, Taiwan off-shore quake and other quakes in past 7 days, 26 Apr 2010, World
name: NEIC, USGS, Taiwan off-shore quake and other quakes in past 7 days, 26 Apr 2010, World
description: The point shapefile shows location of Taiwan's off-shore quake of 6.5 magnitude, followed by a much smaller after shock nearly at the same place at a depth of less than 7 miles. It also shows other quakes of magnitude 2.5 or more in the U.S. and 4.5 or more for the rest of the world over the last 7 days.   Look elsewhere on Finder! and Maker! for quake related data and maps. Use key word "quake", "earth quake"
